The author expresses gratitude to the Senate for confirming Julien X. Neals as a judge for the U.S. District Court for the District of New Jersey and Regina M. Rodriguez as a judge for the U.S. District Court for the District of Colorado with bipartisan support. The author believes that both nominees embody professional excellence and devotion to the rule of law and the Constitution. The author also mentions that there are other nominees awaiting confirmation with bipartisan support. Additionally, the author is thankful for being on track to have the most judges confirmed by July in the first year of a President's term in over 50 years. The author looks forward to making nominations at a historic pace and working closely with the Senate on more confirmations.